TaxIPP is a microsimulation model.
This model mixes survey data and administrative data to get a representative sample of households. The data is then injected into OpenFisca to analyse the impact of a tax & benefit system on households.

TAXIPP is used by the IPP (The Institute for Public Policy) which animate public debate since 2012.

Among other subjects, TaxIPP analyses the French government Finance Law every year. 

